            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; and the notes at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 40:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). The idea is, that their counsels and plans were perverse and evil. We have a similar expression now when we say of a man that he is 'straightforward,' meaning that he is an honest man. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
